Changed some words around to avoid the awkward phrase “real name.” I believe the original writer was using it to mean ‘birth name,’ but 1) I'm not sure why we need to know these people's birth names when they are known far better by other names and 2) “real” insinuates that their stage names are ‘fake,’ which carries a negative connotation. Instead of removing the birth names entirely though, I think this is a good compromise.
